normalized_query: SELECT dstAssetId, extract(responseBody, ?) as title, CAST(count(*) AS Int64), max(recordTimestamp) as maxRecordTimestamp, any(if(position(url, ?) > ?, substring(url, ?, position(url, ?) - ?), url)) As url FROM business.http_log WHERE recordTimestamp >= ? AND recordTimestamp < ? AND respContentType = ? AND respStatus = ? AND position(responseBody, ?) > ? GROUP BY dstAssetId, title LIMIT ?;

SELECT toDate(recordTimestamp) AS report_date, log.srcIp, countIf(respStatus >= ? AND respStatus < ?) AS success_count, countIf(respStatus < ? OR respStatus >= ?) AS fail_count, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus >= ? AND respStatus < ? THEN uri END) AS success_uris, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus < ? OR respStatus >= ? THEN uri END) AS fail_uris, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus >= ? AND respStatus < ? THEN host END) AS success_hosts, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus < ? OR respStatus >= ? THEN host END) AS fail_hosts, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus >= ? AND respStatus < ? THEN dstIp END) AS success_dst_ips, count(DISTINCT CASE WHEN respStatus < ? OR respStatus >= ? THEN dstIp END) AS fail_dst_ips FROM business.http_log AS log WHERE log.srcIpTag = ? AND log.srcIp IS NOT NULL AND log.srcIp != ? AND recordTimestamp >= toDateTime(?) AND recordTimestamp <= toDateTime(?) GROUP BY report_date, log.srcIp ORDER BY report_date DESC, log.srcIp FORMAT CSVWithNames
